BRAZIL: Brazil posts $334 million trade deficit in July.Brazil posts $334 million trade deficit in July.Brazil posted a $334 million trade deficit in July, with exports totalling $4.459 billion and imports at $4.793 billion, the Ministry of Industry and Commerce said in a statement.  The ministry said July results brought the year-to-date trade gap to $630 million, versus a deficit of $4.226 billion in the January-July period of 1995.It said that the July exports were 11.36 percent higher than in July a year ago, and represented the highest export figure ever recorded in that month.Imports were up 19.8 percent over July 1995, it said.In July 1995, Brazil posted a $3.0 million trade surplus.-- Michael Christie, Brasilia newsroom 5561-223-0358